Class Headphone

  • java.lang.Object
    • equipment.Equipment
      • equipment.Headphone
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public abstract class Headphone
extends Equipment
    Headphone class. A headphone is an equipment with an impedance, a frequencyResponse and a soundPressure. initial code by: Marc Karassev; modified by: Marc Karassev
    Author:
    Marc Karassev
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      Headphone()
      Default constructor, constructs a new headphone with an impedance of 30 Ohms, a frequency response of 20 to 20000 Hz, a sound pressure of 100 dB and unknown manufacturer and model.
      Headphone(java.lang.String maker, int imp, java.lang.String resp, int pres, Model type)
      Constructs a new headphone with the specified manufacturer, impedance, frequency response, sound pressure and model.
